description:
&lt;p&gt;The Occupational Therapy service at Pilgrim Hospital provides a service to people in hospital who are experiencing difficulties with occupational performance. The focus of intervention is to promote independence, choice and dignity whilst in hospital and upon their discharge whilst operating within the Hospital Discharge service: Policy and Operating Model 2020. We aim to facilitate patients to be discharged at the earliest opportunity having reached an level of occupational functioning that can be managed in the community. The occupational therapy service is based in three teams covering orthopaedics and surgery; elderly care, medicine and A&amp;E; and stroke.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a qualified Occupational Therapist to join our well-established team of over 30 Occupational Therapy staff. You will work as a part of an Occupational Therapy team with a caseload of patients in surgery, medicine or stroke.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers an important opportunity and challenging career move for you to prove your clinical skills and knowledge. As a department we are committed to excellence and provide regular staff supervision and appraisal. The department takes occupational therapy students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to meeting the requirements of the person specification, the successful applicant will: - Be a qualified Occupational Therapist registered with the HCPC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Have enthusiasm for the profession and working in an acute/secondary care environment - Have a commitment to person-centred care and occupation-focused practice - Be able to work as part of a team - Have well-developed written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Sara Blackbourn&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: sara.blackbourn@ulh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01205 446683&lt;/p&gt;
